171. Am J Hematol. 1984 Apr;16(3):235-42. doi: 10.1002/ajh.2830160305.

An analysis of prognostic factors in preleukemia: interest of bone marrow 
scintigraphy.

Chomienne C, Najean Y, Vigneron N, Dresch C, Rain JD.

Simultaneous bone marrow scintigraphy with 99m Technetium colloids and 111 
Indium transferrin was performed on 34 cases of preleukemic anemias and was 
shown to be of good prognostic value. Groups of different outcome were defined: 
for a normal and parallel uptake of the two markers, 90% of the patients died of 
acute leukemia; for a low Indium and high Technetium uptake, only 1 patient out 
of 15 died of leukemia (P less than 0.001). Standard clinical and hematological 
data were of no predictive value. Iron kinetic data and CFU/GM colony growth 
were correlated to the scintigraphic results. Taken together, these three 
kinetic parameters have a good sensitivity and specificity for the prognosis of 
preleukemic states.

