in 19 patients (p less than 0.05 in nine patients, 0.05 less than p less than 
0.1 in four patients) and slight decreases in four (p less than 0.05 in one 
patient). Doubling time of CT levels calculated from the regression line in each 
patient showed the highest correlation with 3-year survival, recurrence within 5 
years, and time interval between surgery and clinical recurrence of the tumor, 
allowing quantitative prediction of the prognosis.

